{
  "texts": [
    "In Table 4, we explain in detail the number of samples selected for each topic.",
    "These topics were chosen for further analysis as they are fundamental concepts in graduatelevel chemistry courses and are also taught in other disciplines, which can help us achieve a wider point of view of the capabilities of the LLM.",
    "The chemistry questions used in this study were derived from proprietary graduate-level chemistry textbooks, and they were adapted for an adversarial testing environment by transforming them into prompts designed to challenge the model.",
    "This approach was inspired by the work of Talanquer (2023), who conducted a detailed analysis of how ChatGPT generates responses, particularly in challenging scenarios.",
    "Their work categorized the model's output into two key types: \"misconceptions and biases\", where the model produces incorrect or biased information, and \"pressing for more information\", which occurs when the model tries to refine its response by either acknowledging limitations or, in some cases, fabricating information."
  ]
}